Define forecast window¶

In [3]:
# A variable for predicting 'n' days out into the future
n_ahead = 30 #'n=30' days

Get variable of interest for forecast¶

In [4]:
close_px = dataset[['Date','Adj Close']].copy() # creates data frame with two columns
close_px = close_px.loc[close_px['Date'] >= '2005'] # select values that are more significant based on the date

Define independent variable (X)¶

In [5]:
X = close_px['Adj Close'].values.reshape(-1,1) # Returns an array containing the same data with a new shape
X = X[:-n_ahead] # array excludes last 'n' days

Define dependent variable (y)¶

In [6]:
close_px['Prediction'] = close_px['Adj Close'].shift(-n_ahead) # adds new column to data frame. Values = 'Adj Close' but shifted up 'n' days
y = close_px['Prediction'].values.reshape(-1,1)
y = y[:-n_ahead]

Split training & testing data¶

In [7]:
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=0)

Linear regression: define, train & test¶

In [8]:
linear_reg = LinearRegression()  # create Linear Regression Model
linear_reg.fit(X_train, y_train) # training the algorithm
linear_reg_confidence = linear_reg.score(X_test, y_test) # Testing Model: Score returns the coefficient of determination R^2 of the prediction. The best possible score is 1.0
print('Linear Regression confidence: ', linear_reg_confidence)

Linear Regression confidence:  0.9797224884964625

SVR - rbf: define, train & test¶

In [9]:
svr_rbf = SVR(kernel='rbf', C=1e3, gamma=0.1) # create Support Vector Regression SVR - radial basis function rbf
svr_rbf.fit(X_train, y_train) # train
svr_rbf_confidence = svr_rbf.score(X_test, y_test) # Testing Model: Score returns the coefficient of determination R^2 of the prediction. The best possible score is 1.0
print('SVR confidence: ', svr_rbf_confidence)

# Quadratic Regression 2
qda_poly2 = make_pipeline(PolynomialFeatures(2), Ridge())

qda_poly2_confidence = qda_poly2.score(X_test, y_test)
print('Quadratic regression 2 confidence: ', qda_poly2_confidence)

Define series to predict¶

In [12]:
X_2_forecast = close_px['Adj Close'].values.reshape(-1,1) # assign values
n_ahead_2 = int(np.round(n_ahead/2.0))
X_2_forecast = X_2_forecast[-n_ahead:-n_ahead_2] # array includes half 'n' days. The other half will be used for comparison
